Project Overview
This project is a full-stack Medical Document Management System. It allows users to upload, view, download, and delete PDF documents. The backend is built using Node.js and Express, and SQLite is used to store document metadata. The frontend is built using React with Vite.

Tech Stack

~Frontend:

React (Vite)

JavaScript

CSS

~Backend:

Node.js

Express

SQLite

Multer

How to Run the Project Locally

Step 1: Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/d3vpratap/IMI8_LABS.git

cd IMI8_LABS

Step 2: Start the Backend
cd backend
npm install
node server.js

Backend runs on:
http://localhost:5050

Step 3: Start the Frontend
Open a new terminal:
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev

Frontend runs on:
http://localhost:5173

API Endpoints

POST /documents/upload
Upload a PDF document

GET /documents
Fetch all uploaded documents

GET /documents/:id
Download a document

DELETE /documents/:id
Delete a document

